<br>
Ethics of buying and selling aside, I'm really curious as to how you think a buyer can protect themselves.  A determined seller can take the account back at any time.  <br>
<br>
Affliction has recently had two very painful account revocations - two very high playtime, active and dedicated members had their accounts revoked.  It's to the point where I have lobbied the guild to prohibit the inclusion of any new members who are not the original owners.<br>
<br>
I have no desire to spend any time/effort gearing/leveling a character for the benefit (monetary or otherwise) of some third party original owner.<br>
<br>
I briefly checked the forums at playerauctions.com, and all I see is post after post of &quot;scammer!&quot; &quot;I got scammed!&quot; &quot;Don't buy from this person!&quot;  I don't see any helpful information to prevent the original owner from taking back an account.  The only helpful tips I see are instructions in locating &quot;reputable sellers.&quot; This is only helpful if the seller is the original account owner, some of these accounts have had multiple previous owners.<br>
<br>
As I posted earlier, I actually had an account revoked on me as well.  Way back in Kunark, I bought a 34 wizard/29 druid account for help with ports.  I didn't spend a lot of money on it and actually hadn't used it much after Velious.  I was quite surprised that anyone would care enough about some dopey lowbie account to come back after it 18 months after the purchase.<br>
