<br>
Gloriana:  I think your are cool, but did you check the &quot;Fraud Tips and Advice&quot;?  There are a pretty fair number of rules that I follow when I purchase an account to avoid being ripped off.  However, I payed HEAVILY to learn them, and it's part of why people to come to me to buy and sell instead of doing it themselves, so it's not really information that I choose to disseminate publicly.  However as I &quot;grew up&quot; on this server, I will answer specific questions people might have privately at barhorst@bowlofmice.com.<br>
<br>
<br>
Transferring Characters:<br>
Sometime after Luclin they started to red flag any account that had it's billing changed from the original owner.  Pretty much any account that has a server request change (except going TO Legends) is now not only subject to review, but if you don't answer their questions immediately, they want a request from the original owner, oftimes from the original email address, and also with some or all of the following:<br>
Original owner's<br>
Credit card info<br>
Borth Date<br>
Zip Code<br>
Etc etc...any info you signed up with.<br>
<br>
If you want to actually move a character from one account to another, you have to buy EQ and all of the expansions and create a fresh blank account to receive.  You will still run into the same problems though.<br>
<br>
The funny part is that it doesn't happen evey time.  I can only attribute that to lazy bastards at VI customer service blowing off their duties to go play AO or something.<br>
<br>
<br>
Buying a character is as dangerous as you make it.<br>
<br>
